  <description type="morphology">Aerial stems  dimorphic; vegetative stems green, branched, 16--50 cm; hollow center 1/6--1/3 stem diam.  Sheaths  somewhat elongate, 3--5 × 2--4 mm; teeth 8--18, narrow, 1.5--4 mm, centers dark and margins white.  Branches  in regular whorls, horizontal to drooping, solid; ridges 3; valleys channeled; 1st internode of each branch equal to or longer than subtending stem sheath; sheath teeth deltate.  Fertile stems  brown, with stomates, initially unbranched, persisting and becoming branched and green after spore discharge.</description>
